main event: A witness observed a round white object with a small amount of sparks in the sky for 2-3 seconds.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on January 8, 1956, at 0120Z,The object was observed from a distance of 5 miles southwest of Roseburg,The object was noted to have a diameter of 1 foot,It was concluded that the sighting was astronomical,No photographs were taken.
